{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1103,"text":"How do we build a society"},{"time":4253,"text":"without fossil fuels?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6944,"text":"This is a very complex challenge,"},{"time":9920,"text":"and I believe developing countries\ncould take the lead in this transition."},{"time":15120,"text":"And I'm aware that this\nis a contentious statement,"},{"time":18440,"text":"but the reality is that so much\nis at stake in our countries"},{"time":23760,"text":"if we let fossil fuels stay\nat the center of our development."},{"time":29240,"text":"We can do it differently."},{"time":32200,"text":"And it's time, it really is time,"},{"time":35480,"text":"to debunk the myth"},{"time":38200,"text":"that a country has to choose\nbetween development on the one hand"},{"time":43280,"text":"and environmental protection,\nrenewables, quality of life, on the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49800,"text":"I come from Costa Rica,\na developing country."},{"time":52680,"text":"We are nearly five million people,"},{"time":56200,"text":"and we live right in the middle\nof the Americas,"},{"time":58800,"text":"so it's very easy\nto remember where we live."},{"time":63080,"text":"Nearly 100 percent of our electricity"},{"time":70400,"text":"comes from renewable sources,"},{"time":72880,"text":"five of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":78800,"text":"Hydropower, geothermal,"},{"time":82680,"text":"wind, solar, biomass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"Did you know that last year,"},{"time":89160,"text":"for 299 days,"},{"time":92640,"text":"we did not use any fossil fuels"},{"time":95880,"text":"in order to generate all our electricity?"},{"time":100240,"text":"It's a fantastic achievement,"},{"time":104360,"text":"and yet, it hides a paradox,"},{"time":111080,"text":"which is that nearly 70 percent"},{"time":114160,"text":"of all our energy consumption is oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119880,"text":"Why?"},{"time":121800,"text":"Because of our transportation system,"},{"time":124560,"text":"which is totally dependent\non fossil fuels,"},{"time":127840,"text":"like it is in most countries."},{"time":130479,"text":"So if we think of the energy\ntransition as a marathon,"},{"time":134040,"text":"the question is, how do we get\nto the finish line,"},{"time":137960,"text":"how do we decarbonize\nthe rest of the economy?"},{"time":141880,"text":"And it's fair to say\nthat if we don't succeed,"},{"time":144800,"text":"it's difficult to see who will."},{"time":146600,"text":"So that is why I want\nto talk to you about Costa Rica,"},{"time":150160,"text":"because I believe we are a great candidate"},{"time":152880,"text":"in pioneering a vision\nfor development without fossil fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159200,"text":"If you know one thing about our country,"},{"time":162480,"text":"it's that we don't have an army."},{"time":165440,"text":"So I'm going to take you back to 1948."},{"time":169400,"text":"That year, the country\nwas coming out of civil war."},{"time":174360,"text":"Thousands of Costa Ricans had died,"},{"time":177960,"text":"and families were bitterly split."},{"time":181240,"text":"And yet, a surprising idea\nwon the hearts and minds:"},{"time":186280,"text":"we would reboot the country,"},{"time":188200,"text":"and that Second Republic\nwould have no army."},{"time":191280,"text":"So we abolished it."},{"time":193360,"text":"And the president at the time,"},{"time":196040,"text":"Jos√© Figueres,"},{"time":198240,"text":"found a powerful way\nby smashing the walls of an army base."},{"time":205200,"text":"The following year, 1949,"},{"time":208400,"text":"we made that decision permanent\nin the new constitution,"},{"time":212600,"text":"and that is why I can tell you that story\nnearly 70 years later."},{"time":217520,"text":"And I'm grateful."},{"time":219560,"text":"I'm grateful they made that decision\nbefore I was born,"},{"time":223280,"text":"because it allowed me\nand millions of others"},{"time":225560,"text":"to live in a very stable country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229200,"text":"And you might be thinking\nthat it was good luck,"},{"time":232160,"text":"but it wasn't."},{"time":233680,"text":"There was a pattern of deliberate choices."},{"time":238080,"text":"In the '40s, Costa Ricans were given\nfree education and free health care."},{"time":244160,"text":"We called that social guarantees."},{"time":246760,"text":"By abolishing the army,"},{"time":248400,"text":"we were able to turn military spending\ninto social spending,"},{"time":253360,"text":"and that was a driver of stability."},{"time":256120,"text":"In the '50s --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257399,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262600,"text":"In the '50s, we started\ninvesting in hydropower,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and that kept us away from the trap"},{"time":268680,"text":"of using fossil fuels\nfor electricity generation,"},{"time":271760,"text":"which is what the world\nis struggling with today."},{"time":275160,"text":"In the '70s we invested in national parks,"},{"time":278720,"text":"and that kept us away"},{"time":281640,"text":"from the deeply flawed logic\nof growth, growth, growth at any cost"},{"time":286320,"text":"that you see others embracing,\nespecially in the developing world."},{"time":290800,"text":"In the '90s, we pioneered payments\nfor ecosystem services,"},{"time":294920,"text":"and that helped us reverse deforestation"},{"time":296880,"text":"and boosted ecotourism,\nwhich today is a key engine of growth."},{"time":301000,"text":"So investing in environmental protection"},{"time":303960,"text":"did not hurt our economy."},{"time":306200,"text":"Quite the opposite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307480,"text":"And it doesn't mean we are perfect,"},{"time":309520,"text":"and it doesn't mean\nwe don't have contradictions."},{"time":311880,"text":"That's not the point."},{"time":313720,"text":"The point is that,\nby making our own choices,"},{"time":317240,"text":"we were able to develop resilience\nin dealing with development problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324080,"text":"Also, if you take a country like ours,"},{"time":327680,"text":"the GDP per capita\nis around 11,000 dollars,"},{"time":331600,"text":"depending on how you measure it."},{"time":334080,"text":"But according to\nthe Social Progress Index,"},{"time":336160,"text":"we are an absolute outlier"},{"time":338080,"text":"when it comes to turning GDP\ninto social progress."},{"time":342000,"text":"Abolishing the army,"},{"time":343560,"text":"investing in nature and people,"},{"time":345400,"text":"did something very powerful, too."},{"time":349120,"text":"It shaped the narrative,"},{"time":352000,"text":"the narrative of a small country\nwith big ideas,"},{"time":354640,"text":"and it was very empowering\nto grow up with that narrative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359520,"text":"So the question is,"},{"time":361720,"text":"what is the next big idea\nfor this generation?"},{"time":366320,"text":"And I believe what comes next"},{"time":368720,"text":"is for this generation\nto let go of fossil fuels for good,"},{"time":375640,"text":"just as we did with the army."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378400,"text":"Fossil fuels create climate change."},{"time":380720,"text":"We know that,"},{"time":382120,"text":"and we know how vulnerable we are\nto the impacts of climate change."},{"time":386640,"text":"So as a developing country,\nit is in our best interest"},{"time":390320,"text":"to build development without fossil fuels"},{"time":392320,"text":"that harm people in the first place."},{"time":396880,"text":"Because"},{"time":399000,"text":"why would we continue importing oil"},{"time":403800,"text":"for transportation"},{"time":405560,"text":"if we can use electricity instead?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408720,"text":"Remember,"},{"time":410560,"text":"this is the country"},{"time":412480,"text":"where electricity\ncomes from water in our rivers,"},{"time":418560,"text":"heat from volcanoes,"},{"time":421080,"text":"wind turbines, solar panels,"},{"time":424440,"text":"biowaste."},{"time":426560,"text":"Abolishing fossil fuels means\ndisrupting our transportation system"},{"time":432880,"text":"so that we can power our cars,\nbuses and trains with electricity"},{"time":438240,"text":"instead of dirty energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440400,"text":"And transportation, let me tell you,"},{"time":442840,"text":"has become an existential issue\nfor us Costa Ricans,"},{"time":446920,"text":"because the model we have\nis not working for us."},{"time":449360,"text":"It's hurting people,"},{"time":451480,"text":"it's hurting companies,"},{"time":453240,"text":"and it's hurting our health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455240,"text":"Because when policies\nand infrastructure fail,"},{"time":460000,"text":"this is what happens on a daily basis."},{"time":464800,"text":"Two hours in the morning,"},{"time":466400,"text":"two hours in the evening."},{"time":468240,"text":"I don't understand why\nwe have to accept this as normal."},{"time":472800,"text":"It's offensive"},{"time":475040,"text":"to have to waste our time like this\nevery single day."},{"time":479920,"text":"And this highway is actually quite good"},{"time":481840,"text":"compared to what you see\nin other countries"},{"time":483920,"text":"where traffic is exploding."},{"time":486000,"text":"You know, Costa Ricans call this \"presa.\""},{"time":489280,"text":"Presa means \"imprisoned.\""},{"time":492360,"text":"And people are turning violent"},{"time":495360,"text":"in a country that is otherwise\nhappy in pura vida."},{"time":500040,"text":"It's happening."},{"time":501880,"text":"So a lot is at stake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504560,"text":"The good news"},{"time":506440,"text":"is that when we talk\nabout clean transportation"},{"time":509480,"text":"and different mobility,"},{"time":510760,"text":"we're not talking about\nsome distant utopia out there."},{"time":515799,"text":"We're talking about electric mobility\nthat is happening today."},{"time":521039,"text":"By 2022, electric cars\nand conventional cars"},{"time":526520,"text":"are expected to cost the same,"},{"time":529520,"text":"and cities are already trying\nelectric buses."},{"time":533800,"text":"And these really cool creatures"},{"time":536760,"text":"are saving money,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and they reduce pollution."},{"time":541480,"text":"So if we want to get rid\nof oil-based transportation, we can,"},{"time":545480,"text":"because we have options now\nthat we didn't have before."},{"time":548120,"text":"It's really exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550760,"text":"But of course,"},{"time":553280,"text":"some get very uncomfortable\nwith this idea,"},{"time":557760,"text":"and they will come and they will tell you"},{"time":560960,"text":"that the world is stuck with oil,\nand so is Costa Rica, so get real."},{"time":565800,"text":"That's what they tell you."},{"time":567080,"text":"And you know what the answer\nto that argument is?"},{"time":569440,"text":"That in 1948, we didn't say\nthe world is stuck with armies,"},{"time":573040,"text":"so let's keep our army, too."},{"time":575000,"text":"No, we made a very brave choice,"},{"time":578640,"text":"and that choice made the whole difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581600,"text":"So it's time for this generation\nto be brave again"},{"time":586000,"text":"and abolish fossil fuels for good."},{"time":587800,"text":"And I'll give you three reasons\nwhy we have to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591240,"text":"First,"},{"time":593120,"text":"our model of transportation\nand urbanization is broken,"},{"time":596880,"text":"so this is the best moment\nto redefine our urban and mobility future."},{"time":602520,"text":"We don't want cities\nthat are built for cars."},{"time":605360,"text":"We want cities for people"},{"time":607720,"text":"where we can walk and we can use bikes."},{"time":611600,"text":"And we want public transportation,"},{"time":613760,"text":"lots of it,"},{"time":615280,"text":"public transportation\nthat is clean and dignifying."},{"time":619200,"text":"Because if we continue\nadding fleets of conventional cars,"},{"time":624760,"text":"our cities will become unbearable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"Second, we have to change,"},{"time":629760,"text":"but incremental change\nis not going to be sufficient."},{"time":634720,"text":"We need transformational change."},{"time":637600,"text":"And there are some\nincremental projects in my country,"},{"time":640480,"text":"and I am the first one to celebrate them."},{"time":643800,"text":"But let's not kid ourselves."},{"time":646200,"text":"We're not talking about ending up\nwith really beautiful electric cars here"},{"time":650120,"text":"and a few electric buses there"},{"time":652760,"text":"while we keep investing\nin the same kind of infrastructure,"},{"time":656160,"text":"more cars, more roads, more oil."},{"time":658680,"text":"We're talking about\nbreaking free from oil,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and you cannot get there\nthrough incrementalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668360,"text":"Third, and you know this one,"},{"time":673080,"text":"the world is hungry for inspiration."},{"time":678120,"text":"It craves stories of success"},{"time":681240,"text":"in dealing with complex issues,"},{"time":683040,"text":"especially in developing countries."},{"time":687400,"text":"So I believe Costa Rica\ncan be an inspiration to others,"},{"time":691720,"text":"as we did last year when we disclosed"},{"time":694480,"text":"that for so many days\nwe were not using any fossil fuels"},{"time":698480,"text":"in order to generate all our electricity."},{"time":703360,"text":"The news went viral around the world."},{"time":707640,"text":"Also, and this makes me extremely proud,"},{"time":710760,"text":"a Costa Rican woman, Christiana Figueres,"},{"time":715480,"text":"played a decisive role in the negotiations\nof the Paris climate agreement."},{"time":722600,"text":"So we have to protect that legacy\nand be an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727400,"text":"So what comes next?"},{"time":730240,"text":"The people."},{"time":732280,"text":"How do we get people to own this?"},{"time":735760,"text":"How do we get people"},{"time":737880,"text":"to believe that it's possible"},{"time":740320,"text":"to build a society without fossil fuels?"},{"time":744040,"text":"A lot of work from\nthe ground up is needed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749120,"text":"That is why, in 2014,\nwe created Costa Rica Limpia."},{"time":753720,"text":"\"Limpia\" means \"clean,\""},{"time":756440,"text":"because we want to empower\nand we want to inspire citizens."},{"time":760760,"text":"If citizens don't get engaged,"},{"time":765080,"text":"clean transportation decisions\nwill be bogged down by endless,"},{"time":769760,"text":"and I mean endless, technical discussions,"},{"time":772760,"text":"and by avalanches of lobbying\nby various established interests."},{"time":780720,"text":"Wanting to be a green country\npowered by renewables"},{"time":784600,"text":"is already part of our story."},{"time":787200,"text":"We should not let anybody\ntake that away from us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792080,"text":"Last year, we brought people\nfrom our seven provinces"},{"time":796560,"text":"to talk about climate change\nin terms that matter to them,"},{"time":800720,"text":"and we also brought this year"},{"time":803640,"text":"another group of Costa Ricans"},{"time":805720,"text":"to talk about renewable energy."},{"time":807840,"text":"And you know what?"},{"time":809120,"text":"These people disagree on almost everything"},{"time":811400,"text":"except on renewable energy"},{"time":814080,"text":"and clean transportation and clean air."},{"time":816200,"text":"It brings people together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818200,"text":"And the key to real participation"},{"time":821080,"text":"is to help people not to feel small."},{"time":823320,"text":"People feel powerless,"},{"time":824640,"text":"and they are tired of not being heard."},{"time":829000,"text":"So what we do is concrete things,"},{"time":831400,"text":"and we translate technical issues\ninto citizen language"},{"time":835920,"text":"to show that citizens have a role to play\nand can play it together."},{"time":840480,"text":"For the first time, we're tracking\nthe promises that were made"},{"time":843720,"text":"on clean transportation,"},{"time":845240,"text":"and politicos know\nthat they have to deliver it,"},{"time":847880,"text":"but the tipping point will come\nwhen we form coalitions --"},{"time":851960,"text":"citizens, companies,"},{"time":853840,"text":"champions of public transportation --"},{"time":856040,"text":"that will make electric mobility\nthe new normal,"},{"time":858840,"text":"especially in a developing country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862560,"text":"By the time the next election comes,"},{"time":866280,"text":"I believe every candidate\nwill have to disclose where they stand"},{"time":869720,"text":"on the abolition of fossil fuels."},{"time":871640,"text":"Because this question\nhas to enter our mainstream politics."},{"time":876520,"text":"And I'm telling you,\nthis is not a question of climate policy"},{"time":880000,"text":"or environmental agenda."},{"time":882760,"text":"It's about the country that we want"},{"time":886160,"text":"and the cities that we have"},{"time":888280,"text":"and the cities that we want"},{"time":889960,"text":"and who makes that choice."},{"time":892160,"text":"Because at the end of the day,\nwhat we have to show"},{"time":895360,"text":"is that development with renewable energy"},{"time":898520,"text":"is good for the people,"},{"time":901440,"text":"for Costa Ricans that are alive today"},{"time":903880,"text":"and especially for those\nwho haven't been born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909560,"text":"This is our National Museum today."},{"time":912640,"text":"It's bright and peaceful,"},{"time":914360,"text":"and when you stand up in front of it,"},{"time":917080,"text":"it's really hard to believe\nthese were military barracks"},{"time":920400,"text":"at the end of the '40s."},{"time":922600,"text":"We started a new life\nwithout an army in this place,"},{"time":926440,"text":"and here is where our abolition"},{"time":930320,"text":"of fossil fuels will be announced one day."},{"time":933240,"text":"And we will make history again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935560,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936800,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}